# Execution Guardrails

## Resource Constraints

| Item | Limit | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `max_parallel_teammates` | <e.g., 3> | <e.g., matches the parallel fan-out in workflow.md mermaid> |
| `total_wall_clock_budget` | <e.g., 10 min> | <e.g., upper bound for one full run including all sequential stages> |
| `total_token_budget` | <e.g., 200k tokens> | <e.g., budget across all roles; prevents one teammate from exhausting context> |
| `<per_role_token_budget>` (optional) | <e.g., 60k per role> | <only if asymmetric — e.g., the curator role gets more than analysts> |
| `<per_role_wall_clock>` (optional) | <e.g., 3 min per role> | <only if asymmetric> |
| `debate_rounds` (Debate pattern only) | <e.g., 1–2> | Cross-exam round count; each round ≈ linear token growth |

## Behavioral Constraints

<Team-level rules — distinct from per-role Boundary which constrains a single role.
Behavioral Constraints govern what Leader and the team-as-a-whole must / must not do.>

- **Leader-as-orchestrator only**: the Leader dispatches teammates and integrates outputs.
  The Leader does NOT write findings, run analyses, or substitute any role's work.
- <Pattern-specific isolation rule:
  A-pattern: "Teammates MUST NOT see each other's output during their work — isolation is the value of adversarial review."
  C-pattern: "Each stage MUST NOT modify upstream stage outputs — only enhance / annotate."
  B-pattern: "Each parallel role works on its assigned slice ONLY — slices are dispatch-time fixed, not negotiated."
  Debate-pattern: "Round 1 teammates are isolated (no cross-visibility). Round 2+ teammates receive prior-round outputs from all other roles (mutual visibility). The Teamskill declares who sees whose output at which phase; how it is delivered is a framework-level choice with recommended preference: (1) direct peer-to-peer exchange; (2) shared blackboard; (3) Leader-relay as fallback.">
- **Contradiction handling**: when roles disagree, Leader surfaces contradictions verbatim
  in the Final Report. Leader NEVER mediates / picks a winner / averages opinions.
  Resolution is the human user's call.
- <Domain-specific behavioral rule, e.g., "no live-system testing without authorization"
  for security-audit-team, "blameless language only" for incident-response-team, etc.>

## Failure Handling

### (a) Teammate failure

| Failure mode | Response |
|---|---|
| Teammate timeout | Retry once (single retry only). On 2nd timeout, mark role's section in the Final Report as `[ROLE MISSING — teammate timed out]` and proceed with the remaining roles' outputs. |
| Malformed teammate output (does not match Output Schema) | Re-dispatch with the schema explicitly inlined and a "your previous output was malformed" preamble. Max 1 retry. On 2nd malformed output, mark as `[ROLE MISSING — malformed output]` and proceed. |
| Teammate refuses (e.g., claims it cannot find anything for an A-pattern adversarial role) | Re-dispatch with the role's `Boundary > Mandatory` rule restated. If it still refuses, mark as `[ROLE INCONCLUSIVE]` and surface verbatim in the report. |

### (b) Input over-scale degradation

| Trigger condition | Degraded mode |
|---|---|
| <e.g., diff > 2000 LOC> | <e.g., fall back to single-role mode using only the most critical role; warn the user before starting> |
| <e.g., topic too narrow for B-pattern decomposition> | <e.g., reduce to 1 role; warn user that the team's value is reduced> |
| <e.g., critical dependency missing per pre-flight> | <e.g., user already chose to proceed in Step 0 — record the missing dep in the Final Report> |

### Escalation rules

- If 50%+ of roles return `[ROLE MISSING]`, the run is **FAILED** — emit a partial report with explicit "FAILED: insufficient role coverage" header and surface to user.
- If `total_wall_clock_budget` is exceeded, halt all in-flight teammates, emit whatever partial outputs exist, and tag the report `INCOMPLETE: budget exceeded`.
- If `total_token_budget` is exceeded mid-run, halt new dispatches, allow in-flight to complete, emit partial report tagged `INCOMPLETE: token budget exceeded`.

